148":"1148","1203":"1203","1201":"1201","1179":"1179","1243":"1243","1144":"1144","1175":"1175","about 1174":"about 1174","England":"England, United Kingdom","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","Barlow, Chorlton, Lancashire, England":"Chorlton, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","Chorlton, Lancashire, England":"Chorlton, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Barlow","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of several places called Barlow, especially those in Lancashire and Yorkshire. The former is named with Old English <i>bere</i> ‘barley’ + <i>hlāw</i> ‘hill’; the latter probably has as its first element the derived adjective <i>beren</i> or the compound <i>bere-ærn</i> ‘barn’. There is also a place of this name in Derbyshire, named with Old English <i>bār</i> ‘boar’ or <i>bere</i> ‘barley’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’, and one in Shropshire, which is from <i>bere</i> ‘barley’ + <i>lēah</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Barlowe","meanings":["English: variant of   Barlow  ."]}]},{"name":"Christopher","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Greek name <i>Khristophoros</i>, from <i>Khristos</i> ‘Christ’ + <i>pherein</i> ‘to bear’. This was popular among early Christians, conscious of the fact that they were metaphorically bearing Christ in their hearts. A later, over-literal interpretation of the name gave rise to the legend of a saint who actually bore the Christ-child over a stream; he is regarded as the patron of travellers. In England the name was uncommon in the Middle Ages, but became very popular in the 16th century, especially in parts of the North."],"variants":[{"name":"Kristopher","meanings":["Mainly U.S.: respelling of   Christopher ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Christopher Barlow was born in 1175, in Chorlton, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Sir Robert Barlow, was 32 and his mother, Lady Ursula Berron, was 27. He had at least 1 son with Margaret Gamble. He died in 1243, in his hometown, at the age of 68."},"et":{"1175–1243":"1175–1243","1179–1243":"1179–1243","1206–Male":"1206–Surnud","1144–1203":"1144–1203","1148–1201":"1148–1201","June 1203":"juuni 1203","1206":"1206","1148":"1148","1203":"1203","1201":"1201","1179":"1179","1243":"1243","1144":"1144","1175":"1175","about 1174":"umbes 1174","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Barlow, Chorlton, Lancashire, England":"Chorlton, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Chorlton, Lancashire, England":"Chorlton, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1175–1243":"1175–1243","1179–1243":"1179–1243","1206–Male":"1206–Kuollut","1144–1203":"1144–1203","1148–1201":"1148–1201","June 1203":"kesäkuu 1203","1206":"1206","1148":"1148","1203":"1203","1201":"1201","1179":"1179","1243":"1243","1144":"1144","1175":"1175","about 1174":"noin 1174","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Barlow, Chorlton, Lancashire, England":"Chorlton, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Chorlton, Lancashire, England":"Chorlton, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1175–1243":"1175–1243","1179–1243":"1179–1243","1206–Male":"1206–Décédé","1144–1203":"1144–1203","1148–1201":"1148–1201","June 1203":"juin 1203","1206":"1206","1148":"1148","1203":"1203","1201":"1201","1179":"1179","1243":"1243","1144":"1144","1175":"1175","about 1174":"environ 1174","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Barlow, Chorlton, Lancashire, England":"Chorlton, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Chorlton, Lancashire, England":"Chorlton, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Christopher Barlow est né en 1175, à Chorlton,